SIMPLE: corticotropin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: corticotropin
<hw>corticotropin</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>a growth hormone produced by the anterior pituitary gland; it
stimulates the adrenal cortex; -- called also
<altname>adrenocorticotropin</altname> and abbreviated
<altname>ACTH</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> adrenocorticotropic hormone, adrenocorticotrophic
hormone, adrenocorticotropin, adrenocorticotropin, corticotrophin,
ACTH.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corticous</ent>⟦br⟧
